ewell', 'The Lighthouse' & 'Ford v Ferarri' Among Best Film Mentions |publisher=[[Seattle Film Critics Society]] |date=December 9, 2019 |accessdate=December 10, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191210132341/https://www.awardscircuit.com/2019/12/09/seattle-film-critics-society-nominations-the-farewell-the-lighthouse-ford-v-ferarri-among-best-film-mentions/ |archive-date=December 10, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://seattlefilmcritics.com/2019/12/16/parasite-named-best-picture-of-2019-by-seattle-film-critics-society/|title=\"Parasite\" Named Best Picture of 2019 by Seattle Film Critics Society|first=Seattle Film|last=Critics|date=December 16, 2019|accessdate=January 24, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| Best action choreography\n| {{nominated}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"1\"| Southern Eastern Film Critics Association\n| rowspan=\"1\"| December 10, 2019\n| Top 10 films of 2019\t\n| vertical-align: middle; text-align: center; \" class=\"a\" rowspan=\"1\"|''Ford v Ferrari'' \n| {{won}}\n| rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://collider.com/sefca-winners-2019-parasite/|title=Southeastern Film Critics Association Selects 'Parasite' as the Year's Best Film|first=Matt|last=Goldberg|date=December 9, 2019|accessdate=January 24, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"1\"| [[18th Visual Effects Society Awards|Visual Effects Society Awards]]\n|January 29, 2020\n|Outstanding Supporting Visual Effects in a Photoreal Feature\n|Olivier Dumont, Kathy Siegel, Dave Morley, Malte Sarnes, Mark Byers\n|{{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/01/ves-awards-nominations-2020-list-the-lion-king-the-mandalorian-game-of-thrones-1202823016/|title=VES Awards Nominations: 'The Lion King', 'Alita: Battle Angel', 'The Mandalorian' & 'GoT' Top List|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|first=Patrick|last=Hipes|date=January 7, 2020|accessdate=January 7, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/