{"title_page": "Lynn Kelly", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n'''Lynn Kelly''' (born 1957) is a New Zealand jewellery designer. Her work is in the permanent collection of [[Museum of New Zealand Te Papa Tongarewa]], the [[Dowse Art Museum]] and [[Auckland War Memorial Museum]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://collections.tepapa.govt.nz/agent/6298|title=Loading... {{!}} Collections Online \u2013 Museum of New Zealand Te Papa Tongarewa|website=collections.tepapa.govt.nz|access-date=18 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.thebigidea.nz/connect/media-releases/2014/mar/139671-artist-to-make-park-jewels|title=Artist to make 'park jewels'|date=18 March 2014|website=The Big Idea|language=en|access-date=18 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Biography ==\nKelly was originally a gardener, and studied for a certificate in craft design at [[Wanganui Regional Community College]] when she worked for the college's groundskeeping team.<ref name=\":2\" /> She began making jewellery in1988 using precious metals, organic materials and sometimes fossilised plants.<ref name=\":0\" /> Her work is distinctive for recreating the forms of ferns, seed pods and flowers in metals.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\nIn 2004, Kelly won the Molly Morpeth Canaday Wear Aotearoa Award.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.form.co.nz/lynn-kelly|title=Lynn Kelly|website=Form Gallery|language=en-NZ|access-date=18 April 2020}}</ref> She had work represented in the 2nd, 3rd and 4th Jewellery Biennale exhibitions, and in 2007 she won the Dowse Foundation Gold Award.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=http://dowse.org.nz/news/media-releases/2008/kelly-wins-dowse-foundation-gold-award|title=Kelly wins Dowse Foundation Gold Award {{!}} The Dowse Art Museum|website=dowse.org.nz|language=en|access-date=18 April 2020}}</ref> In 2012 Kelly received a Wild Creations residency from [[Creative New Zealand]] and the [[Department of Conservation (New Zealand)|Department of Conservation]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mch.govt.nz/mi/wild-creations-2012-residency-winners|title=Wild Creations 2012 residency winners {{!}} Ministry for Culture and Heritage|website=mch.govt.nz|access-date=18 April 2020}}</ref> In 2014 she was Artist-in-Residence for [[Auckland City Council]] at [[Scandrett Regional Park]].<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kelly, Lynn}}\n[[Category:1957 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:New Zealand jewellers]]\n", "text_old": "'''Lynn Kelly''' (born 1957) is a New Zealand jewellery designer. Her work is in the permanent collection of [[Museum of New Zealand Te Papa Tongarewa]], the [[Dowse Art Museum]] and [[Auckland War Memorial Museum]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://collections.tepapa.govt.nz/agent/6298|title=Loading... {{!}} Collections Online - Museum of New Zealand Te Papa Tongarewa|website=collections.tepapa.govt.nz|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.thebigidea.nz/connect/media-releases/2014/mar/139671-artist-to-make-park-jewels|title=Artist to make 'park jewels'|date=2014-03-18|website=The Big Idea|language=en|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref>\n\n== Biography ==\nKelly was originally a gardener, and studied for a certificate in craft design at Wanganui Regional Community College when she worked for the college's groundskeeping team.<ref name=\":2\" /> She began making jewellery in1988 using precious metals, organic materials and sometimes fossilised plants.<ref name=\":0\" /> Her work is distinctive for recreating the forms of ferns, seed pods and flowers in metals.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\nIn 2004, Kelly won the Molly Morpeth Canaday Wear Aotearoa Award.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.form.co.nz/lynn-kelly|title=Lynn Kelly|website=Form Gallery|language=en-NZ|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref> She had work represented in the 2nd, 3rd and 4th Jewellery Biennale exhibitions, and in 2007 she won the Dowse Foundation Gold Award.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=http://dowse.org.nz/news/media-releases/2008/kelly-wins-dowse-foundation-gold-award|title=Kelly wins Dowse Foundation Gold Award {{!}} The Dowse Art Museum|website=dowse.org.nz|language=en|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref> In 2012 Kelly received a Wild Creations residency from [[Creative New Zealand]] and the [[Department of Conservation (New Zealand)|Department of Conservation]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mch.govt.nz/mi/wild-creations-2012-residency-winners|title=Wild Creations 2012 residency winners {{!}} Ministry for Culture and Heritage|website=mch.govt.nz|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref> In 2014 she was Artist-in-Residence for [[Auckland City Council]] at [[Scandrett Regional Park]].<ref name=\":0\" />\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kelly, Lynn}}\n[[Category:1957 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:New Zealand jewellers]]\n", "name_user": "Schwede66", "label": "safe", "comment": "fixeddashesusing ascript, date formats perMOS:DATEFORMATbyscript", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lynn_Kelly"}
